31/01/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat have achieved significant progress in resumed talks to reunify the divided island, UN Special Envoy for Cyprus Alexander Downer announced on Friday (January 29th).
The statement came after another round of intensified negotiations and ahead of a planned visit by UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon on Sunday.
Ban will meet both Christofias and Talat in an effort to boost momentum in the talks.
(Famagusta Gazette - 30/01/10;
BBC, Xinhua - 29/01/10)
